obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (24067)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24067&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Delhi Primary Education`
  line `Act, 1960.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the Union territory of Delhi.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the State Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 2nd October, 1960, vide notification No. S.O. 2391(E), dated 27th September, 1960, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (24068)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24068&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "academic year" means the year beginning on such date as a local authority may specify with`
  line `respect to any specified area or with respect to approved schools generally or any approved school or`
  line `class of approved schools in particular within its jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(b) "approved school" means any school in any specified area within the jurisdiction of a local`
  line `authority imparting primary education which—`
  line
  line `(i) is under the management of the State Government or the local authority, or`
  line
  line `(ii) being under any other management, is recognised by the local authority as an approved`
  line `school for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "attendance authority" means any person appointed to be an attendance authority under`
  line `section 7;`
  line
  line `(d) "to attend an approved school" means to be present for instruction at an approved school on`
  line `so many days in a year and at such time or times on each one of those days as may be fixed by the`
  line `local authority concerned;`
  line
  line `(e) "child" means a boy or girl within such age group, not being less than six or more than`
  line `fourteen, as may be specified in a declaration made under section 4;`
  line
  line `(f) "local authority" means the Municipal Corporation of Delhi, the New Delhi Municipal`
  line `Committee and the Delhi Cantonment Board;`
  line
  line `(g) "parent", in relation to any child, includes a guardian and every person who has the actual`
  line `custody of the child;`
  line
  line `(h) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) "primary education" means education up to such class or standard, not beyond the eighth class`
  line `or standard, as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(j) "rural areas" shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 2 of the Delhi Municipal`
  line `Corporation Act, 1957 (66 of 1957);`
  line
  line `(k) "special school" means any institution which imparts such primary education as is in the`
  line `opinion of the State Government suitable for children suffering from any physical or mental defect;`
  line
  line `(l) "specified area" means any area within the jurisdiction of a local authority in which primary`
  line `education is declared by that authority to be compulsory under section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (24069)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Schemes for primary education.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24069&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of every local authority to provide for`
  line `compulsory primary education for children ordinarily resident within its jurisdiction, and for this purpose`
  line `it shall, from time to time, submit to the State Government such proposals in the form of a scheme as it`
  line `may think fit providing for such compulsory primary education in the whole or any part of the area within`
  line `its jurisdiction for children of such ages and up to such class or standard as it may decide.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the State Government may, at any time,`
  line `call upon a local authority to submit to it within such time as may be specified a scheme for compulsory`
  line `primary education in such area within the jurisdiction of the local authority for children ordinarily`
  line `resident therein, and of such ages and up to such class or standard, as the State Government may specify.`
  line
  line `(3) The scheme submitted under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be in such form as the State`
  line `Government may specify and shall contain the following particulars,—`
  line
  line `(a) the area in which primary education shall be compulsory;`
  line
  line `(b) the approximate number of children to whom the scheme will apply, classified according to`
  line `age and mother-tongue;`
  line
  line `(c) a list of existing approved schools and the schools, if any, proposed to be opened for the`
  line `purpose, classified by languages in which instruction is given or is proposed to be given;`
  line
  line `(d) the number of teachers already employed and the additional staff proposed to be recruited;`
  line
  line `(e) the recurring and non-recurring cost of the scheme; and`
  line
  line `(f) such other particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government may, after making such inquiry as it may consider necessary, sanction with`
  line `or without modifications the scheme submitted by the local authority under sub-section (1) or sub-section`
  line `(2).`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (24070)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Primary education to be compulsory in areas covered by schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24070&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of sanction`
  line `under sub-section (4) of section 3, the local authority shall give effect to the scheme so sanctioned by`
  line `means of a declaration that with effect from the first day of the next academic year primary education`
  line `shall be compulsory in any area specified in the declaration for children ordinarily resident in that area`
  line `and within such age group and up to such class or standard as may be specified in the declaration.`
  line
  line `(2) Every declaration under sub-section (1) shall—`
  line
  line `(a) be published in the Official Gazette and in such other manner as the local authority may`
  line decide;
  line
  line `(b) be so made as to ensure that there is an interval of not less than one hundred and twenty days`
  line `between the date of the publication of the declaration and the first day of the next academic year.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (24071)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title Grants-in-aid.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24071&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The State Government shall, in respect of every scheme sanctioned under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 3 or prepared under sub-section (1) of section 17, bear such part of the recurring`
  line `and non-recurring cost of the scheme as it may from time to time determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (24072)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Duty of local authority to prepare lists of children.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24072&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of the local authority to`
  line `cause to be prepared as early as possible after the publication of a declaration under section 4, and in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed, a list of children in any specified area; and the local authority shall cause`
  line `the list to be revised at such intervals as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (24073)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Attendance authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24073&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The local authority may appoint as many persons as it thinks fit to`
  line `be attendance authorities for the purposes of this Act, and may also appoint as many persons as it`
  line `considers necessary to assist the attendance authorities in the discharge of their duties.`
  line
  line `(2) In the exercise of any of the powers conferred by or under this Act, the attendance authority or`
  line `any person appointed to assist the attendance authority may put such questions to any parent or require`
  line `any parent to furnish such information, about his child as it or he considers necessary, and every such`
  line `parent shall be bound to answer such questions or to furnish such information, as the case may be, to the`
  line `best of his knowledge or belief.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (24074)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Attendance authority to notify parent of his obligation towards his child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24074&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty`
  line `of the attendance authority to notify the parent of every child to whom the declaration under section 4`
  line `applies that he is under an obligation to cause the child to attend an approved school with effect from the`
  line `beginning of the next academic year.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (24075)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Responsibility of parent to cause his child to attend school.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24075&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of the parent`
  line `of every child to cause the child to attend an approved school unless there be a reasonable excuse for his`
  line `non-attendance within the meaning of section 10.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (24076)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Reasonable excuse for non-attendance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24076&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Act, any of the following`
  line `circumstances shall be deemed to be a reasonable excuse for the non-attendance of a child at an approved`
  line school,—
  line
  line `(a) that there is no approved school within the prescribed distance from his residence;`
  line
  line `(b) that the child is receiving instruction in some other manner which is declared to be`
  line `satisfactory by the State Government or by an officer authorised by it in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) that the child has already completed primary education up to the class or standard specified in`
  line `the declaration under section 4;`
  line
  line `(d) that the child suffers from a physical or mental defect which prevents him from attendance;`
  line
  line `(e) that there is any other compelling circumstance which prevents the child from attending`
  line `school, provided the same is certified as such by the attendance authority;`
  line
  line `(f) such other circumstance as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (24077)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Special schools for physically or mentally deficient children.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24077&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `If there is in existence a special`
  line `school within the prescribed distance from the residence of a child who is suffering from a physical or`
  line `mental defect, the attendance authority may, if it is satisfied that the child is not receiving any instruction`
  line `in some other manner considered by it to be satisfactory, by order require the child to attend the special`
  line `school; and it shall be the duty of the parent of such child to cause the child to attend the special school`
  line `unless there be a reasonable excuse for the non-attendance of the child within the meaning of clause (e) of`
  line `section 10.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (24078)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Special provision for part-time education in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24078&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the attendance authority is`
  line `satisfied that a child, due to economic or other circumstances connected with the family to which the`
  line `child belongs, is unable to attend an approved school in the manner required by or under this Act, it may,`
  line `by order and subject to such conditions, if any, as it may think fit to impose, permit the child to attend any`
  line `approved school established as a part-time institution or in which primary education is imparted on a`
  line `part-time basis.`
  line
  line `(2) Any parent who causes a child in respect of whom an order under sub-section (1) has been made`
  line `to attend an approved school in the manner specified in the order shall be deemed to have complied with`
  line `the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (24079)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Attendance orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24079&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever the attendance authority has reason to believe that the parent`
  line `of a child has failed to cause the child to attend an approved school and that there is no reasonable excuse`
  line `for the non-attendance of the child within the meaning of section 10, it shall hold an inquiry in the`
  line `prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(2) If as a result of the inquiry the attendance authority is satisfied that the child is liable to attend an`
  line `approved school under this Act and that there is no reasonable excuse for his non-attendance within the`
  line `meaning of section 10, it shall pass an attendance order in the prescribed form directing the parent to`
  line `cause the child to attend the-approved school with effect from the date specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(3) An attendance order passed against a parent in respect of his child under this section shall, subject`
  line `to the provisions of sub-section (6), remain in force for so long as this Act continues to apply to the child.`
  line
  line `(4) If any parent against whom an attendance order has been passed in respect of his child under`
  line `sub-section (2) transfers the custody of the child to another person during the period in which the`
  line `attendance order is in force, such parent shall be bound to immediately inform the attendance authority in`
  line `writing of such transfer.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an attendance order has been passed against a parent in respect of his child under this`
  line `section, such order shall have effect in relation to every other person to whom the custody of the child`
  line `may be transferred during the period in which the attendance order is in force as it has effect in relation to`
  line `the person against whom it is passed.`
  line
  line `(6) A parent may at any time apply to the attendance authority for cancellation of an attendance order`
  line `on the ground—`
  line
  line `(i) that he is no longer the parent in respect of the child; or`
  line
  line `(ii) that circumstances have arisen which provide a reasonable excuse for non-attendance;`
  line
  line `and thereupon the attendance authority may, after holding an inquiry in the prescribed manner, cancel or`
  line `modify the attendance order.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (24080)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Children not to be employed so as to prevent them from attending school.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24080&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `No person shall`
  line `employ a child in a manner which shall prevent the child from attending an approved school.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (24081)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Primary education to be free.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24081&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) No fee shall be levied in respect of any child for attending an`
  line `approved school which is under the management of the State Government or a local authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, in respect of any child an attendance order has been passed under section 13 and the only`
  line `school which he can attend is an approved school under private management falling within sub-clause (ii)`
  line `of clause (b) of section 2, the local authority shall take such steps as it may think fit for the purpose of`
  line `ensuring that the primary education which the child is to receive is free.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (24082)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Age of child how to be computed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24082&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The age of a child for the purposes of this Act shall be`
  line `computed in terms of years completed by the child on or before the first day of the academic year:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the birthday of a child falls on a day not later than sixty days from the first day of`
  line `the academic year, the birthday shall be deemed to fall on the first day of the academic year for the`
  line `purpose of computing the age of the child.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (24083)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Failure of local authority to prepare or implement scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24083&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any local authority when`
  line `called upon to submit a scheme under sub-section (2) of section 3 fails so to do, or, after a scheme has`
  line `been sanctioned under sub-section (4) of section 3 fails to give effect to a scheme as so sanctioned,`
  line `whether wholly or in part, the State Government may, after making such inquiry as it may consider`
  line `necessary and after giving an opportunity to the local authority to be heard in the matter, appoint any`
  line `person to prepare the scheme or to give effect to it, as the case may be, and may direct that such part of`
  line `the expenses as that Government may determine shall be defrayed out of the funds belonging to the local`
  line authority.
  line
  line `(2) Where any such direction as is referred to in sub-section (1) is issued, any person who has for the`
  line `time being the custody of any moneys on behalf of the local authority, either as a banker or in any other`
  line `capacity, shall, notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force, be bound to`
  line `comply with such direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (24084)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Penalty for contravention of section 13.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24084&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any parent fails to comply with an attendance`
  line `order passed under section 13. he shall be punishable with fine not exceeding two rupees, and, in the case`
  line `of a continuing contravention, with an additional fine not exceeding fifty naye paise for every day during`
  line `which such contravention continues after conviction for the first of such contraventions:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount of fine payable by any one person in respect of any child in any one year`
  line `shall not exceed fifty rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person fails to furnish any information as required by sub-section (4) of section 13, he shall`
  line `be punishable with fine which may extend to twenty-five rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (24085)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Penalty for contravention of section 14.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24085&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `If any person contravenes the provisions of`
  line `section 14, he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to twenty-five rupees and, in the case of a`
  line `continuing contravention, with an additional fine not exceeding one rupee for every day during which`
  line `such contravention continues after conviction for the first of such contraventions.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (24086)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Courts competent to try offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24086&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The courts competent to try offences under this Act shall`
  line `be the following,—`
  line
  line `(a) in rural areas to which the Delhi Panchayat Raj Act, 1954 (Delhi Act III of 1955) extends, the`
  line `Panchayati Adalat, constituted under section 50 of that Act, within whose jurisdiction the person`
  line `committing the offence resides;`
  line
  line `(b) in other areas, the court of a magistrate having jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) Any offence triable by the Panchayati Adalat shall be tried in the manner provided for the trial of`
  line `criminal cases by the Delhi Panchayat Raj Act, 1954 (Delhi Act III of 1955), and any offence triable by a`
  line `magistrate shall be tried in a summary way.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (24087)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24087&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `No court shall take cognizance of an offence under this Act except on`
  line `the complaint of an attendance authority or any other person authorised in this behalf by the local`
  line `authority by general or special order.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (24088)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Certain persons to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24088&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The attendance authority, every person appointed to`
  line `assist the attendance authority under sub-section (1) of section 7 and every person authorised to make`
  line `complaints under section 21 shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (24089)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24089&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Government or any authority or person in respect of anything which is in good faith done`
  line `or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (24090)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24090&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette`
  line `and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification, authorise any officer or`
  line `authority subordinate to it to exercise all or any of the powers conferred on the State Government by or`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A local authority may, by general or special order and with the previous approval of the State`
  line `Government, authorise any officer or authority subordinate to it to exercise all or any of the powers`
  line `conferred on a local authority by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (24091)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24091&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette`
  line `and subject to the condition of previous publication, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the class or standard education up to which shall be considered as primary education;`
  line
  line `(b) the particulars to be contained in any scheme submitted under this Act, including particulars`
  line `relating to the provision made or to be made in any area for the establishment of special schools or of`
  line `schools imparting primary education on a part-time basis or for the supply of food or refreshments,`
  line `books, writing materials, uniforms or other necessary amenities, to children while attending school;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which lists of children may be prepared in any specified area under section 6,`
  line `the intervals at which the lists shall be kept revised and persons with whose assistance such lists shall`
  line `be prepared;`
  line
  line `(d) the functions to be performed, and the manner in which such functions may be performed, by`
  line `attendance authorities;`
  line
  line `(e) the distance beyond which a child may not be compelled to attend an approved school;`
  line
  line `(f) the circumstances which may be regarded as reasonable excuses for the non-attendance of a`
  line `child within the meaning of section 10;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner in which any inquiry under this Act may be held;`
  line
  line `(h) the form in which an attendance order under this Act may be passed;`
  line
  line `(i) the registers, statements and other information to be maintained or furnished by approved`
  line `schools for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session in which it is so laid or the`
  line `session immediately following, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses`
  line `agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or`
  line `be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (24092)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Repeal of Punjab Primary Education Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675&sectionId=24092&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00003_196039_1517807319675
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `On the date on which primary education becomes`
  line `compulsory in any specified area, the Punjab Primary Education Act, 1940 (Punjab Act XVIII of 1940) as`
  line `in force in the Union territory of Delhi shall stand repealed in such area.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
